{"lemma":"جُزُر","slug":"جُزُر","root":"ج.ز.ر","root_slug":"ج-ز-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ج-ز-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n5652","n5685","n5689","n5690","n5691"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AC%D9%8F%D8%B2%D9%8F%D8%B1"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"carrots","tags":["collective","uncountable"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to slaughter","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to kill, to butcher (an animal)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَزَرَ (jazara, “slaughter”)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"slaughter"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"butchering"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to fall; to ebb (of water)","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of جَزَرَ (jazara, “ebb”)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ebb (of the sea)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"plural of جَزِيرَة (jazīra)","tags":["form-of","plural"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Persian گزر (gazar).\n\nForm I verb and verbal noun."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n5652","headword_ar":"جزّر","root":"jz","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf.n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tajoziyzN","text_ar":"تَجْزِيزٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He dried"},{"kind":"text","text":"dates. (Msb.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n5685","headword_ar":"جَزَرَ","root":"jzr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazorN","text_ar":"جَزْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cut off,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, K,) a thing. (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazara","text_ar":"جَزَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb,) [inf. n. as above,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He slaughtered"},{"kind":"text","text":"a camel (S, Mgh, Msb) or other animal, (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and skinned"},{"kind":"text","text":"it; (S;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajtzr","text_ar":"اجتزر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazara lahumo","text_ar":"جَزَرَ لَهُمْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He slaughtered for them a camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawoma jazuwrFA","text_ar":"القَوْمَ جَزُورًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ajtzr","text_ar":"اجتزر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He slaughtered and skinned for the people a camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazara Aln~axola","text_ar":"جَزَرَ النَّخْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazorN","text_ar":"جَزْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazaArN","text_ar":"جَزَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jizaArN","text_ar":"جِزَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut off the fruit of the palm-trees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lh, S, K:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he spoiled the palm-trees in fecundating them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazara","text_ar":"جَزَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazorN","text_ar":"جَزْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gathered"},{"kind":"text","text":"honey from the hive. (K, TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazara","text_ar":"جَزَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazorN","text_ar":"جَزْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K, &c.,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(water)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sank, and disappeared; became low;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became remote;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"decreased; went away;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flowed away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh, * Msb,) from the earth, or land: (A, Mgh:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"(the sea, and a river, Lth, ISd)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ebbed; contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mad~a","text_ar":"مَدَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, ISd, K; [but in this last sense, only"},{"kind":"text","text":"is authorized by the K, and app. by ISd also, as the aor.; ]) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"retreated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"went back;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S. Msb; *) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Anjzr","text_ar":"انجزر","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (ISd, TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ceased to increase."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Mgh.)"}],"source_refs":["K","Mgh","S","Msb","Lh","TA","A"]},{"entry_id":"n5689","headword_ar":"جَزْرٌ","root":"jzr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of 1. (S, K, &c.)       -A2-  And also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sea"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) itself. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n5690","headword_ar":"جَزَرٌ","root":"jzr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (not ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jizarN","text_ar":"جِزَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", Fr, S, [but see what follows,]) [a coll. gen. n.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fat sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA:) n. un."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazarapN","text_ar":"جَزَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goats, that are slaughtered;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazuwrN","text_ar":"جَزُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) n. un. as above: (M: in the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazorapN","text_ar":"جَزْرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazarapN","text_ar":"جَزَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat, fit for slaughter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sheep,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat, to which the owners betake themselves and which they slaughter:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything that is lawful to be slaughtered;"},{"kind":"text","text":"n. un. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazarN","text_ar":"جَزَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is sometimes [written ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jizarN","text_ar":"جِزَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":",] with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"z","text_ar":"ز"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazaru Als~ibaAEi","text_ar":"جَزَرُ السِّبَاعِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The flesh which beasts or birds of prey eat."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tarakuwhumo jazarFA","text_ar":"تَرَكُوهُمْ جَزَرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They slew them:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"they left them cut"},{"kind":"page_break","n":419},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in pieces"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lils~ibaAEi","text_ar":"لِلسِّبَاعِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"for the beasts or birds of prey"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAruwA jazarFA liloEaduw~i","text_ar":"صَارُوا جَزَرًا لِلْعَدُوِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They became a prey to the enemy, cut in pieces"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Mgh.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaziyrapN","text_ar":"جَزِيرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  Also, and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiz~rN","text_ar":"جِزّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, S, Msb, K,) the latter with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"j","text_ar":"ج"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) arabicized, (K,) from the Persian ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Gazaro","text_ar":"گَزَرْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (AHn,) [coll. gen. ns., meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Carrots,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"carrot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain root,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aruwmap","text_ar":"اَرُومَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is eaten,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"well known:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazarapN","text_ar":"جَزَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (As, S, Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the best kind is the red and sweet, which grows in winter: it is hot in the extreme of the second degree; moist in the first degree;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diuretic;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lenitive; emollient;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strengthening to the venereal faculty; emmenagogue: the putting of its pounded leaves upon festering ulcers is advantageous:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it is difficult of digestion; and engenders bad blood; but is made wholesome with vinegar and mustard."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HinozaAbN","text_ar":"حِنْزَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hzb","text_ar":"حزب"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["S","K","TA","Fr","Msb","AHn","As"]},{"entry_id":"n5691","headword_ar":"جِزَرٌ","root":"jzr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jazarN","text_ar":"جَزَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}